2. cs.GT (Game Theory) - The paper investigates the interplay between knowledge sharing and coalition ability in a concurrent game, which falls under the scope of game theory. 
3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper proposes a new semantics for a temporal logic with imperfect information and perfect recall, which is a topic within logic in computer science. 
4. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with a group of agents forming a coalition, which is a common topic in multi-agent systems research. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper proposes a new semantics for a logic, which could be of interest to researchers in programming languages.
